12
13 4-88-1503. Liability for poultry integrators — Penalties.
14 (a) An owner or operator of a poultry integrator that violates this
15 subchapter is liable if the poultry integrator knowingly engages in an action
16 described under § 4-88-1502(b).
17 (b)(1) As authorized under § 4-88-103, a prosecutor may initiate an
18 enforcement action against the owner or operator of a poultry integrator who
19 allegedly violates § 4-88-1502.
20 (2) As authorized under § 4-88-104, the Attorney General may
21 initiate an enforcement action against the owner or operator of a poultry
22 integrator who allegedly commits a violation of § 4-88-1502.
23 (c) The owner or operator of a poultry integrator that violates this
24 subchapter is, upon conviction, guilty of a Class B felony.
25 (d) A grower who is injured by the violation of this subchapter by a
26 poultry integrator may:
27 (1) File a civil action for damages; and
28 (2) Be awarded damages, fees, costs, and reasonable attorney's
29 fees.
